latestIgtvVideos.title: Checking out some @seeloveindia products
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here are my favourite @seeloveindia products and why I love them - 

1. Calm & Repair Night Crème - ceramides and squalane. What else do I mention? Choose this if you feel your skin lacks moisture and suppleness. 

2. Daily Oil Control Serum - this one contains 10% niacinamide and Zinc PCA. Niacinamide has so many exotic properties like reduce oil secretion, reducing pigmentation and moist using the skin. 

3. Overnight Radiance Serum - this one is with 14% AHA. Meant for gentle exfoliation. The product is mild and fluidic. You need 2-3 drops to literally cover the whole face and neck. 

4. Daily Love Hydration Cream - who doesn’t need a hyaluronic acid cream in their regimen? It’s super hydrating and reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles. 

5. Gentle Makeup Cleansing Oil - tried this as the first step of double cleansing. It’s strips away the makeup and sunscreen well whiteout leaving you dry or dehydrated.

DOUBLE CLEANSING - 
There was once a time when we all believed washing our faces with soap and water was all the cleansing our skin needed before we hit the sack and call it a night. Then double cleansing came along, and our bedtime routines were never the same again. Turns out our usual soap-and-water combo (and face wipes) isn’t going to cut it if we want all that gunk and grime off our face after a full day.

However, If we strip too much of our natural oils, our body can respond by producing more oil that can lead to breakouts and irritation. 

Cleansing lotions are my favourite kind to remove sunscreens and makeup at the end of the day. 

You can try Moiz cleansing lotion as the first step of double cleansing. 

The second layer is your usual face wash. 

Let me know what you’ve been using to double cleanse.
